      • playSoundEffect

        void playSoundEffect(int id)
        Play a sound effect at the player's current location. This is how UI, and player-generated (e.g. mining, woodcutting) sound effects are normally played
        Parameters:
        id - the ID of the sound to play. Any int is allowed, but see SoundEffectID for some common ones

      • playSoundEffect

        void playSoundEffect(int id,
                     int x,
                     int y,
                     int range)
        Play a sound effect from some point in the world.
        Parameters:
        id - the ID of the sound to play. Any int is allowed, but see SoundEffectID for some common ones
        x - the ground coordinate on the x axis
        y - the ground coordinate on the y axis
        range - the number of tiles away that the sound can be heard from

        When shouldDraw is true, 3D bounding boxes will be drawn either for the object under the cursor, or every object on screen according to BoundingBoxAlwaysOnMode
        Parameters:

      • getBoundingBoxAlwaysOnMode

        boolean getBoundingBoxAlwaysOnMode()

      • setBoundingBoxAlwaysOnMode

        void setBoundingBoxAlwaysOnMode(boolean alwaysDrawBoxes)
        Changes how getDrawBoundingBoxes3D() behaves when active. When alwaysDrawBoxes is true, 3D bounding boxes will be drawn. When false, a 3D bounding box will only be drawn for the object under the cursor
        Parameters:
        alwaysDrawBoxes - whether or not to draw every 3D bounding box, when 3D bounding boxes are enabled

      • changeMemoryMode

        void changeMemoryMode(boolean lowMemory)
        Changes how game behaves based on memory mode. Low memory mode skips drawing of all floors and renders ground textures in low quality.
        Parameters:
        lowMemory - if we are running in low memory mode or not
